<br>
<a href="https://warsawtour.pl/de/wie-kommt-man-so-durch-warschau/" target=”_blank”><h2>Traveling around the City</h2></a>
<p>The best way to travel around the city is by public transport - trams, buses, metro and city trains.</p>
<p>There is dedicated app that surves as a route finder and ticket app - jakdojade <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/pl/app/jakdojade/id506795511?mt=8" target=”_blank”>App Store</a>.</p>
<p>You can also use the webpage to see timetables: <a href="https://jakdojade.pl/warszawa/trasa/?locale=en" target=”_blank”>jakdojade.pl</a>.</p>
<p>And you can buy tickets in advance straight from the app and use them latter.</p>
<p>To validate the ticket please scan the QR code <i class="bi bi-qr-code"></i> placed in the vehicle (tram, bus, train) or in a metro gates.</p>
<p>Tickets (normal fairs) - Zone 1 is all you need:</p>

<ul>
    <li>20 minutes 3.40PLN</li>
    <li>75 minutes 4.40PLN</li>
    <li>90 minutes 7.00PLN</li>
    <li>One-day 15PLN</li>
    <li>Three-days 36PLN</li>
    <li>Weekend 24PLN - Valid from 7PM on Friday - till 8AM on Monday</li>
    <li>Group weekend 40PLN - Valid from 7PM on Friday - till 8AM on Monday for a group up to 5 people</li>
</ul>

<br>
<h2>Alcohol policies</h2>
<p>Alcohol consumption in public is not allowed, except in specially designated places such as restaurants, bars or taverns.</p>
<p>In Warsaw there are additional two special zones that drinking is allowed: Bulwary Wiślane (Vistula boulevards) and plaża Poniatówka (Poniatówka beach).</p>

<br>
<h2>Emergency</h2>
<p>Emergency numbers are:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Ambulance: 112 or 999</li>
    <li>Fire brigade: 112 or 998</li>
    <li>Police: 112 or 997</li>
    <li>Embassy of Germany in Warsaw: 22-584-17-00</li>
</ul>


